    <stitle>CALIPER DISC BRAKES - SERVICE INFORMATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>SERVICE INFORMATION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>INTERNATIONAL vehicles are using a redesigned brake caliper. The redesigned calipers are the 2.60 inch
                and 2.88 inch twin piston disc brake caliper Both calipers are inter- changeable as a complete assembly
                with the old design caliper of the same piston size. However, the caliper components are not
                interchangeable. Example: a service kit for a redesigned caliper will not work in the old design caliper
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401610">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0401610" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0401610" filename="../figg04/G0401610.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Redesigned 2.60 and 2.88 Inch Piston Caliper Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
